# Hexagonal boundaries

## Domain isolation (non-negotiable)
- `src/domain/**` imports only: `@domain/*`, `@shared/*`, TS stdlib.
- **Exception:** `@nestjs/common` — allowed **only** for the `@Injectable()` decorator (no other symbols).
- Forbidden in domain: `driving`, `driven`, `drizzle-orm`, `@aws-sdk/*`, `fastify`, `msw`, and any Nest runtime deps.

### Forbidden imports (examples)
```ts
import { Logger } from '@nestjs/common';           // ❌ runtime dep
import { ConfigService } from '@nestjs/config';    // ❌ runtime dep
import { HttpModule } from '@nestjs/axios';        // ❌ runtime dep
import { Injectable, Module } from '@nestjs/common'; // ❌ Module not needed in domain
```

### Allowed imports (examples)
```ts
import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';        // ✅ decorator only
import { EnrollmentRepositoryPort } from '@domain/enrollment/enrollment.repository.port';
import { Platform } from '@domain/shared/types';
```

## Ports
- Ports live in `src/domain/**/*.port.ts`.
- Use `DrivingPort` / `DrivenPort` markers from `@domain/hexagonal`.
- Ports define interfaces; adapters implement them.

## Adapters
- Driving adapters: `src/driving/nest/http/`, `src/driving/nest/sqs/`.
- Driven adapters: `src/driven/drizzle/`, `src/driven/http/`, `src/driven/eventbridge/`.
- Adapters implement ports and are wired via Nest modules.

## Mapping
- DTOs in driving layer; domain types in domain. Map at adapter boundary.
- DB schema in `src/driven/drizzle/schema/`; map to domain types in repository.
